cs.DM, cs.CO, cs.CC, cs.GR, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the problem involves counting paths on a discrete three-dimensional chessboard. 
- cs.CO (Combinatorics) is also a likely category as the problem involves counting and enumerating combinatorial objects (rook paths). 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely as the paper does not focus on the computational complexity of the problem, but rather on the discovery and proof of an explicit formula for the generating series. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely as the paper does not involve any visual or graphical aspects. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely as the paper does not focus on the design or analysis of algorithms or data structures.
